article.description: — Dyson Koehler had 19 points in Weber State's 84-71 victory over Wyoming on Saturday night.
article.headline: Weber State secures 84-71 win against Wyoming
article.linkText: Weber State secures 84-71 win against Wyoming
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- — Dyson Koehler had 19 points in Weber State's 84-71 victory over Wyoming on Saturday night. Koehler had five rebounds for the Wildcats (6-4). Dillon Jones added 17 points while going 6 of 13 and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line, and he also had 11 rebounds and seven assists. Steven Verplancken Jr. had 16 points and shot 5 for 9 (2 for 4 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line. Akuel Kot led the Cowboys (6-4) in scoring, finishing with 24 points. Sam Griffin added 22 points for Wyoming. Brendan Wenzel also had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
